diff:1401464372:1387396776:=1,2d0%0a%3c *[['''Oonsung Oounsung the mechanical cartoon'''->http://cargocollective.com/parkeunyoung/Oongsung-Oongsung-the-mechanical-cartoon]]: I used to feel awkward when people seemed to gaze at me after I passed by them. That might be from an interest, a suspicion, a hatred or just a habitual gesture which is meaningless. But more often than not, it used to trigger a chain of thoughts lurking in the back of my mind, starting from what is wrong with me at the moment, culminating in what's wrong with my whole being. What their gazing means could be nothing while the reaction of viewers would be something matters here because it reveals what s/he is like and what s/he is thinking. %0a%3c %0a
